# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in only what you need.
# `.env` is gitignored — your keys never leave your machine.
#
# This starter runs in TWO tiers:
#   • FREE  — no key at all. `.mcp.json` connects keyless and you get the 8 free
#             Visibly AI tools (keyword classification, SEO checklists/guidance,
#             URL-structure analysis, locations). Ranking data comes from a GSC
#             export you feed to the Python templates (see below). Nothing here
#             is required for the free tier.
#   • PRO   — add a Visibly AI key to unlock all 32 tools (live GSC/GA at 0
#             credits once Google is connected, plus the DataForSEO-backed
#             premium tools). See docs/setup.md for how to wire the key.

# --- Visibly AI MCP (OPTIONAL — only needed for the PRO tier) ----------------
# Get your key from https://visibly-ai.com (Account → API Keys). Keys look like
# `lc_...`. Leave this unset to run the free tier.
# VISIBLYAI_API_KEY=lc_replace_me

# Optional: pin a default project / workspace if your account has several.
# VISIBLY_AI_PROJECT=

# --- Separately-managed data sources (OPTIONAL, for the keyless free tier) ---
# Without a Visibly key you manage your own data sources. Two common ones:
#
# 1) Google Search Console — the simplest keyless path is a manual export:
#    in GSC export Performance → Queries to CSV, then feed it to the Python
#    template:  python -m claude_tools.status_quo --gsc gsc_query.csv ...
#    (No credentials needed here — the CSV is the interface.)
#
# 2) DataForSEO — if you add the DataForSEO MCP to .mcp.json (see docs/setup.md)
#    for keyword volumes / SERP data, put its credentials here.
#    No account yet? Sign up: https://dataforseo.com/?aff=186597
# DATAFORSEO_LOGIN=
# DATAFORSEO_PASSWORD=
